            . I am a clerk in the Imperial fire-office, Sun-court, Cornhill; Mr. 
               <persName id="t18320105-4-person169">
                  Joseph 
                  Reid
               <interp inst="t18320105-4-person169" type="surname" value="Reid"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320105-4-person169" type="given" value="Joseph"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320105-4-person169" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             is the <rs id="t18320105-4-viclabel23" type="occupation">manager</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18320105-4-victim162 t18320105-4-viclabel23"></join> of that office. (Looking at a letter) the direction on this letter is in my hand-writing - it has the signature of Mr. Reid to it - on the 21st of November I enclosed in this letter two Bank post-bills, one for 300l. and the other for 50l.; here are two of the same amount in it: I received them from the hands of Mr. Ingall, the actuary - I sealed the letter, after enclosing the bills, and directed it to Mrs. 
               <persName id="t18320105-4-person170">
                  Elizabeth 
                  Carkeet
               <interp inst="t18320105-4-person170" type="surname" value="Carkeet"></interp>
